Closing arguments in the case of former SAA board chairperson Dudu Myeni continued at the High Court in Pretoria today. Advocate Carol Steinberg submitted that Dudu Myeni's alleged misconduct, deserves a minimum of over 7 years imprisonment.Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Former South African Airways Dudu Myeni deserves a minimum of over seven-years imprisonment. This was the argument made by advocate Carol Steinberg, who represents the Organisation Undoing Tax Abuse (Outa) and the SAA Pilots’ Association (Saapa). Outa and Saapa want the court to declare Myeni a delinquent director. WATCH: Closing arguments in Myeni delinquent case “We say that the evidence has conclusively demonstrated that Ms Myeni's conduct was delinquent...” said Steinberg. Steinberg added that such conduct warranted a "lifelong declaration of delinquency."